args: Y'know, I'm fine with guard duty and all,\nbut I can't imagine who'd be dense enough\nto try and sneak into Closeheide right now.
Nobody, that's who. And plus, the general's\nhere right now, so they'd have to be\nEXTRA— Wait. Somebody's coming.
Well, hello there, you studly soldier boys.\nI've just got some quick little errands to\ntake care of in town, so if you don't mind...
No entry beyond this point!\nBegone immediately or you will\nbe cut down where you stand!
That's no way to talk to a lady!\nWon't you pleeease let me through?
Hmph. Spare me the sweet talk.\nYou aren't getting through here, ma'am.
Weeell, what can you do? Oh, you ARE\na naughty little kitten. Heh heh heh...
And you REALLY won't let this naughty\nlittle kitten pass? Even after she's been\nsweeter than a saucer of warm milk?
A-all right, I guess it's fine. It's not like\nyou're a complete stranger, after all. But\nno causing trouble! You hear me, kitten?
(Whoever said Closeheide was ＂impossible\nto infiltrate＂ clearly hadn't met Lady\nStarfall!)
Why, thank you EVER so much, my big,\nstrong soldier boys. Bye-bye, now!
Hey, come on! Don't kiss and run!\nLet's have a little more fun together!
We will have PLENTY of quality time soon,\nbelieve me. I simply can't put these\nerrands off any longer, darling.
Who cares about errands?! You've lit a fire\nin me, and it's not goin' out anytime soon!\nYou have to—
Just what EXACTLY does she have to do,\nsoldier?
Why, of course we'd— Wait, hold up!\nY-you're...
Dereliction of duty. Debauchery. Indolence.\nThis is a stain on your honor as soldiers.\nYou should be ashamed.
(He...he's Valyx! What's an imperial\ngeneral doing out in a backwater 'burb like\nthis?!)
(His presence is fearsome indeed. There's\nno way I can take him in a head-on fight.\nBluff, Malora, bluff...)

Further, I can scarcely believe you'd
be charmed by this woman, an ally of the
Halidom, and not realize your indiscretion!
Am I mistaken, woman?
(Urk! The jig is up! He's not just strong—\nhe's sharp, too! Nothing's going to get\npast him.)
Are you deaf, soldiers?\nArrest this woman. Immediately.
Will you not resist? You've some backbone.\nOr perhaps it's something else.\nWell, it matters not. Come.
S-sir, if there's to be an interrogation,\nwe wouldn't want to trouble you.\nWe will carry it out for y—
You wouldn't be able to handle it.\nI will question her myself.
You're as docile as a lamb.\nWhat are you plotting, woman?
Nothing at all. Tied up as I am, I hardly\nthink myself capable of anything, much\nless mustering up some grand scheme.
What I want to know is what you plan to\ndo with me.

Following your interrogation, I'll be
sending you to prison in the capital.
Look well upon the light of day,
for you will never see it again.
My, you underestimate me. You think\nyou can keep ME under lock and key?

Did you not see your soldiers? It would be
a simple task for me to bewitch my jailers
and see myself whisked far away from
your prison.
Indeed it would. A strong case for dealing\nwith you right here and now, in fact.
I can do you one better. A great and\npowerful general needs a partner, does he\nnot? In public...and in private, I daresay?
If you spare me, I will spy on your behalf.\nI will bring you any information you desire,\nno matter how classified.
And I will obey all of your orders without\nquestion, whether they pertain to work\nor matters more...discreet.
You think these honeyed words will sway\nme? I am quite sure you've already sworn\nfealty to my brother.

That I found myself in the employ of
{player_name} is mere
happenstance. And what's more, he...
does not truly understand me.
He is much too soft. He has not once given\nme a task that utilizes my ample talents.\nHe coddles me like a pitiful hatchling.
He never so much as steals a sidelong\nglance at me. His impertinence has\nsent me into a crisis of self-esteem.

I wish to serve one who will both
understand and make ample use of my
considerable talents. I care not the form
that arrangement takes.

YOU would certainly not show amnesty to a
former enemy, would you? That's the kind
of man I'd like to serve—one unafraid
to raise a stern hand.
If you do not believe me, then test them\nfor yourself. We are alone right now. Give\nme any order at all, and I will obey.
Hmph. You allowed yourself to be captured\nwithout a fuss because you were confident\nyou could bewitch me.
You planned to find an opening and\nescape, or to win me over. Whichever it\nis, you have grossly underestimated me.
D-did you really see through me so easily?
Discipline is the cornerstone of any\nprudent military man. Do not insult me so.
I will ask you this one time: What secret\norders has my brother sent you here to\ncarry out?
I am here by no order of\n{player_name}'s.
Then you come to distinguish yourself of\nyour own volition. What is your aim?\nSpeak honestly, for if you do not...

*sigh* You truly are the real deal. I can ply
you with neither raw might nor feminine
allure. I will tell you everything, so lower
your weapon.
My objective is a necklace, stolen from my\nclient by a deceitful lover. I'm told that it\nwas sold to one Count Delchi.
You infiltrated enemy territory to retrieve a\ntrinket? You might consider a better lie.

Putting your life on the line for a tangle of
foolish passions is laughable. Keep your
secrets, then. I'll have you take them to
your grave.
You are a far more tedious man than the\nreports would suggest, Valyx.

The necklace I speak of was given to my
client by her mother as a keepsake. It's not
the sort of thing whose importance can be
measured against sovereign duty.
And what's more, I absolutely cannot abide\nthe theft of something so precious at the\nhand of false love.
Hmph. You risk your life out of pity, then?\nNaught but naive sentiment.
Unfortunately for you, I am not nearly so\nsaccharine a woman as you take me for.
I'm also here for my own sake. My pride\nwould never allow me to forsake a love\nscorned.
Your ＂pride＂? You are so arrogant that you\nspit in the face of death? Or is that end\nprecisely what you have desired all along?
I-it is assuredly not! Only a fool would\nrush headlong into the hereafter!
Nonetheless, I have no regrets. Where love\nis concerned, I will never yield.
If you're going to kill me, Valyx, then do it.
I see. In that case— HAAAAH!
...You've cut my bonds?\nWhat are you playing at, Valyx?
Even I have heard of Count Delchi's\nfraudulent financial activities.
If your aim in this city is to exact justice\nfor his misdeeds, then I have no reason to\nstop you.
What, so I'm free to move about the city?

I will not impede you, so long as your
movements concern that necklace. That
said, I cannot well allow an enemy to run
about my territory completely unchecked.

As such, I restrict you thus: You have until
sunset. If you cannot accomplish your
objective by then, I will come to deliver
final judgment myself.
Nowhere in this city is beyond my sight.\nShould you fail, I WILL find you.\nRemember that.
I have until sunset, and if I cannot achieve\nmy objective by then, I will meet my end.\nHeh... You drive quite a tough bargain.

If your outlandish pride is genuine, then I
am certain you will accomplish your goal.
Now go, and show me what your words
are worth.
Phew. Talk about a close call. I'm working\nwith quite a handicap now... I need to get\nthat necklace back before sunset.
These Alberian royals certainly are a\nstubborn bunch, aren't they?
